# Data-Network Layer: Remote Data Sources

## Required Orchestration
- When changing an existing feature data-network module, first invoke `.cursor/skills/feature-edit-review-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- Select `data-network-dispatchers` for remote data source, dispatcher, Ktor call, or DTO-layer changes.
- If the change touches shared networking or threading abstractions in `common/**`, also invoke `.cursor/skills/common-module-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- Before completion, invoke `.cursor/skills/repo-verification-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.

## 1) Define contracts + implementations in data-network
- `*-data-network` must define:
  - `interface *RemoteDataSource`
  - and its implementation (e.g. `*RemoteDataSourceImpl`)
- Data-network must not depend on UI/Compose.

## 2) HTTP execution must be off the main thread
- All network calls must be wrapped with the shared dispatcher abstraction (`DispatcherProvider`):
  - `withContext(dispatcherProvider.IO) { ... httpClient ... }`
- Avoid hardcoding `Dispatchers.IO`.

## 3) Use Ktor client + serialization directly
- Prefer typed Ktor flows:
  - `httpClient.get(url).body<SomeDTO>()` (or `.body()` when type is inferred)
- Response DTOs/entities should be `@Serializable` and live in the data-network module.

## 4) Error handling strategy
- Default: let exceptions propagate from remote calls.
  - Use-cases (via `SuspendUseCase` / `FlowUseCase`) will map them into `Resource.Error`.
- Only swallow errors if you implement an explicit “best-effort / partial success” contract at the remote level.

## 5) DI registration
- Register remote data sources in Koin for the corresponding feature/data-network module.
- Use explicit bindings:
  - `factoryOf(::SomeRemoteDataSourceImpl) bind SomeRemoteDataSource::class`

